{
  "texts": [
    "The sentiment analysis prowess of decoder-only models found in this study, is on par with encoder-only according to [20] and [19], and that underscores the practical efficiency of encoder-only models in NLU tasks without the need for generative features.The implications of the above findings underscore the nuanced considerations in selecting model architectures for real-world applications.",
    "While decoder-only models exhibit remarkable generative capabilities, their primary focus may not align with NLU tasks.",
    "For practical and resource-efficient solutions, encoder-only models emerge as a robust choice, excelling in NLU without the need for generative features.",
    "However, it's essential to acknowledge that decoder-only models can serve as an expedient alternative with a few-shot approach, especially when fine-tuning constraints are present, despite a trade-off in final performance.",
    "The colossal scale of newer decoder-only LLMs, while impressive, may not be indispensable for all real-world applications."
  ]
}